emerged on the New York Underground Hip-Hop scene back in 2000 around the end of the golden era. He really started making noise at small clubs in Staten Island, Brooklyn, Long Island, and Upper and Lower Manhattan with his powerful voice, political message, and use of live instruments on production combined with gritty record samples. His energetic an explosive live performances had him almost immediately sought after by many promoters and was soon opening up for acts like Jeru The Damaja, Guru, M1 (Dead Prez), The Beatnuts and more. His group ACL (Audio Composers League) has opened up for some of the biggest names in Hip-Hop such as Wu-Tang Clan, Nas, Common, and more.
In 2007 he independently released his first album 'Archaeology' which he recorded, mixed and mastered in a small room at his parent's house in Long Island. Some notable features included Diabolic (Viper Records) and Tim Williams (front man of acclaimed New York Hard Core band Vision Of Disorder). The album went on to sell over 2,000 hard copies independently, thousands of downloads and millions of plays on myspace and other sites with a zero dollar budget and no distribution just from touring and Internet sales.
After doing some small US tours with The Day Laborers and Opening up some tour dates with Immortal Technique and Diabolic all while engineering Diabolic's debut album 'Liar & A Thief' released on Viper Records and The Day Laborers debut album 'The Learning Process' it was time to do an official solo album.
In 2011 Nightwalker released his solo album Walking At Night on a new independent label called RedPhone Records. The record was produced, engineered, mixed, and mastered by Walker and was highly acclaimed by fans and peers alike.
Now residing on the south side of Chicago he is a highly sought after act for live performances, features, and production having performed at the Metro, Reggie's, Subterranean, The Shrine, Junior's and more.
